article.headline: Price helps Eastern Washington beat Idaho State 79-67 for 7th straight win
article.description: — Ethan Price had 16 points and Eastern Washington won for a seventh straight time, beating Idaho State 79-67 on Saturday night.
article.linkText: Price helps Eastern Washington beat Idaho State 79-67 for 7th straight win
article.story: POCATELLO, Idaho -- — Ethan Price had 16 points and Eastern Washington won for a seventh straight time, beating Idaho State 79-67 on Saturday night. Price was 6 of 11 shooting (2 for 5 from 3-point range) for the Eagles (11-7, 5-0 Big Sky Conference). Jake Kyman shot 4 for 6, including 3 for 3 from beyond the arc to add 13 points. Cedric Coward had 12 points and was 3 of 3 shooting and 5 of 5 from the free throw line. Miguel Tomley led the Bengals (7-12, 2-4) in scoring, finishing with 22 points. AJ Burgin added 16 points for Idaho State. Brayden Parker also had 11 points, seven rebounds, four steals and five blocks. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
